                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/32339: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-16T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 16, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1548. You may inform Foreign Minister, with reference to your 2302, December 15,
                    4 p.m., that this Government considers the declaration <pb facs="0026" n="12"
                        xml:id="pg_12"/> by United Nations a “Declaration”, as stated in the title
                    of the document; that consequently it has not been submitted to the Senate as a
                    treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
